text: Z̀ (minuscule: z̀) is a letter of the Latin alphabet, formed from Z with the addition of a grave accent. It is used in the Old Welsh and Wenzhounese alphabets. ==Encodings== The HTML codes are: * for Z̀ (upper case) List of Latin-based precomposed UNICODE characters with description of their elements ==See also== * Grave accent * rz (digraph) == References == Category:Latin letters with diacritics Category:Phonetic transcription symbols
